e solstice regime. As in the eddy-permitting simulations, a mean-flow feedback\textemdash involving the upper-level zonal winds, the lower-level temperature gradient, and the poleward boundary of the cross-equatorial Hadley cell\textemdash makes it possible for the circulation fields to change at the transition more rapidly than can be explained by the steady-state response to the thermal forcing. However, the regime transitions in the axisymmetric simulations are less sharp than those in the eddy-permitting simulations because eddy\textendash mean flow feedbacks in the eddy-permitting simulations additionally sharpen the transitions.{$<$}/p{$><$}/section{$>$}},
