ed to the trend in the ANET.{$<$}/p{$><$}p{$>$}Another important indicator of the midlatitude circulation is the Arctic Oscillation (AO). Through the 1980s and early 1990s the AO index has shown a positive trend. However, even though a part of the SAT trend can be related to the AO in localized parts of the Arctic area, the mean Arctic SAT trend shows no significant linkage to the AO.{$<$}/p{$><$}/section{$>$}},
