ng case. Very high resolution simulations of the undiffused problem indicate that a k-1 spectrum is approached asymptotically, but only at resolutions corresponding to 106 x 106. The passive scalar behavior is compared and contrasted with the behavior of scalar pseudo-vorticity (an `active scalar') in the family of generalized 2D turbulence models introduced elsewhere in this issue.},
