significant fraction of the interannual variability in some regions cannot he explained by either a zonal index or ENSO. A further important feature of the zonal index in the 1947\textendash 94 period is the recurrence of anomalies over multiyear periods. Such behavior has important implications for decadal climate variations, examples of which are given for secular changes after 1976.},
